    {
      "id": "857389eb_68c239f1",
      "file_path": "catalog-model/src/main/java/org/openecomp/sdc/be/model/Component.java",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 630,
      "message": "Sorry about that, but I have just realized that `Optional.of` could throw a NullPointerException if the passed argument is null. We can fix that with `Optional.ofNullable(list.get(0))`.\n\nSorry again for the inconvenience.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6614,
        "name": "Francis Toth",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "francis.toth@yoppworks.com",
        "username": "francistoth"
      },
      "updated": "2020-04-20 17:13:03.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "ec0f41fe_43532b37",
      "file_path": "catalog-model/src/main/java/org/openecomp/sdc/be/model/Component.java",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 630,
      "message": "It is checked for null though  (list == null || ...) and if it is, Optional.empty() is returned and Optional.of(list.get(0)) is not executed, so cannot get NPE get",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5269,
        "name": "Michael Morris",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "michael.morris@est.tech",
        "username": "MichaelMorris"
      },
      "updated": "2020-04-21 00:42:15.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "857389eb_68c239f1",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "b74585b1_8d8b56a3",
      "file_path": "catalog-model/src/main/java/org/openecomp/sdc/be/model/Component.java",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 630,
      "message": "You are right but it wouldn't hurt use `Optional.ofNullable`. If someone changes the condition without taking care, an NPE could slip in.",
      "author": {
